學分
2

課程大綱
課程目標: 
1.     
Introduction of organizational behavior
2.     
Academic discipline for research capacity on organizational theory
3.     
Discussion and analysis on organizational behavior issues
 
This course is designed to introduce students the systematic
knowledge of organizational behavior, including the patterns of human
interaction, job motivation and satisfaction, perception and decision making,
leaderships in organizations, formal and informal networks in organizations and
so forth. Students would be inspired toward a research design in the field of
organizational theory and its implication. Several issues could be discussed: what
is organizational behavior—how matter the organizational diversity is; how
politics and power operate organizational interaction, how to improve human
resource management under a certain organizational culture and climate. This
course would also open the discussion for students to share their experience in
their workplace.
 
課堂進行方式：(40%) 
1.     
老師講解組織行為理論概念
2.     
學生報告文獻摘要(中文文獻可)
 
期末報告: (60%) 線上繳交時間 6月25日(二)晚上12點截止
以組織行為理論議題為中心，進行研究設計。

教科書
Stephen P. Robbins, &
Timothy A. Judge (2013), Organizational
Behavior, ISBN-13: 9780273765295, ISBN-10: 0273765299





